      <!--Volume of Auto Loan end-->
      <!--Bank of America Personal Loan Chargeoffs, Recoveries section start-->
      <div class="volume-auto-loan loan-chargeoff-recovry">
         <h2 class="tab_blue_content"><%=@bank.name%> Auto Loan Chargeoffs, Recoveries </h2>
         <p> For <%=@bank.name%>'s securitized auto loans, the charge-offs amount to <%= @fdic_cal_data.present? ? number_to_currency((@fdic_cal_data.a_szdrauto * 1000).round(-3), precision: 0) : '$0'%> and the recoveries amount to <%= @fdic_cal_data.present? ? number_to_currency((@fdic_cal_data.a_szcrauto * 1000).round(-3), precision: 0) : '$0'%>.
         <p>
          <!-- a_szcrauto column not -->
         For general car loans, the charge-offs amount to <%= @fdic_cal_data.present? ? number_to_currency((@fdic_cal_data.a_drauto * 1000).round(-3), precision: 0) : '$0'%> and the recoveries amount to <%= @fdic_cal_data.present? ? number_to_currency((@fdic_cal_data.a_crauto * 1000).round(-3), precision: 0) : '$0'%>. This results in a net charge-offs of automobile loans debited to the allowance for loan and lease losses of <%= @fdic_cal_data.present? ? number_to_currency((@fdic_cal_data.a_ntauto * 1000).round(-3), precision: 0) : '$0'%>.
         </p>
         <p>
            An additional figure for loan performance are automobile loans to individuals for household, family and other personal expenditures that are past due  still and accruing interest.
         </p>
         <p class="loan-chargeoff-recovry-inner-data"><span>Past Due 30 -89 days</span> Past Due 90+ days</p>
         <p class="loan-chargeoff-recovry-inner-data"><span><%= @fdic_cal_data.present? ? number_to_currency((@fdic_cal_data.a_p3auto * 1000).round(-3), precision: 0) : '$0'%></span> <%= @fdic_cal_data.present? ? number_to_currency((@fdic_cal_data.a_p9auto * 1000).round(-3), precision: 0) : '$0'%></p>
         <a class="seo-loan-aftr-cntnt-link" href="">Data produced from US Government reported Financials</a>
